They worry that concerns about the virus may have a long-lasting impact on how they make a living.
Customers may be wary of getting too close, no matter how badly they need their nails buffed or hair done.
When she reopens, she'll continue to wear a mask and refrain from crowding the salon to make her clients feel comfortable.
“After this is over, I’m not going to be afraid to go back out there and do hair,'' she says.
"I'm going to try to rest up right now and I will be ready and excited when we do open back up.''